cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.IR 

The paper proposes a deep multimodal fusion network for person identification using multiple modalities such as face, iris, and fingerprint. The proposed algorithm involves the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for feature extraction and fusion. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses joint optimization of the modality-specific CNNs, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with biometric identification, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of iris and fingerprint modalities also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
